  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Method I\r\nFor maximum current, equivalent resistance should be minimum
    so all the bulbs should be\r\nsimultaneously switched on and should be connected
    in parallel. As resistance of the one bulb =V\xB2/p R=1210 ohm \n\nEquivalent
    resistance of the circuit=R/3\n=403.33 Ohm\n\nMaximum current=220/4033.33\n\nMaximum
    current=0.55A\n\nMethod 2\n if all the bulbs are connected in parallel with the
    battery,the potential difference across will ve V=220V.And since the rated power
    is 40W-220V. \nCurrent through each bulb,\n\nI=P/V=40W/220V \n so total current
    through all the three bulbs=3 x(40/220)=0.55A\n"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
